{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1777215862999,"sessionID":"ses_235ae4ddfffeslQpORMPty8nFN","part":{"id":"prt_dca51f473001LZGouWYQ2uDQ7W","messageID":"msg_dca51e361002ZFnqukUhAmnxYz","sessionID":"ses_235ae4ddfffeslQpORMPty8nFN","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_00_1VvtOBH9QxG6EFPfCWaQwwdU","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skill/cli-opencode/SKILL.md"},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skill/cli-opencode/SKILL.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: name: cli-opencode\n3: description: \"OpenCode CLI orchestrator covering three use cases: external AI runtimes dispatching opencode run, in-OpenCode parallel detached sessions for ablation and worker farms, and cross-AI orchestration handback with full plugin, skill, and MCP runtime context.\"\n4: allowed-tools: [Bash, Read, Glob, Grep]\n5: version: 1.0.0\n6: ---\n7: \n8: <!-- Keywords: opencode, opencode-cli, opencode-run, cross-ai, spec-kit-runtime, plugin-runtime, parallel-sessions, share-url, detached-session, agent-delegation, anthropic, openai, google, gemini -->\n9: \n10: # OpenCode CLI Orchestrator - Full-Runtime Cross-AI Dispatch\n11: \n12: > **CRITICAL — SELF-INVOCATION PROHIBITED**\n13: >\n14: > This skill dispatches to the OpenCode CLI binary (`opencode`). If the agent currently reading this skill is itself running inside OpenCode (TUI / acp / serve / run modes — detection signals listed in §2), the skill MUST refuse to load and return the documented error message instead of generating any `opencode` invocation. The only exception is an explicit \"parallel detached\" request that intentionally spawns a SEPARATE session with its own session id and state directory.\n15: >\n16: > Just as a Claude Code agent never calls cli-claude-code, an OpenCode agent never calls cli-opencode, a Codex agent never calls cli-codex, a Copilot agent never calls cli-copilot, and a Gemini agent never calls cli-gemini. The cli-X skills are for **cross-AI delegation only** — never self-invocation.\n17: \n18: Orchestrate OpenCode's `opencode run` from external AI assistants (Claude Code, Codex, Copilot, Gemini, raw shell) AND from inside an existing OpenCode session for parallel detached workers. Three documented use cases keep the cycle risk explicit while giving every dispatch path a copy-paste invocation shape.\n19: \n20: **Core Principle**: The calling AI stays the conductor. Delegate to OpenCode for what it does best — full plugin, skill, MCP, and Spec Kit Memory runtime in a one-shot dispatch. Validate and integrate the output.\n21: \n22: ---\n23: \n24: <!-- ANCHOR:when-to-use -->\n25: ## 1. WHEN TO USE\n26: \n27: ### Activation Triggers\n28: \n29: - **Full plugin / skill / MCP runtime** (use case 1) — calling AI is Claude Code / Codex / Copilot / Gemini / raw shell AND the task needs the project's full Spec Kit Memory database, CocoIndex semantic index, structural code graph, or every plugin/skill/MCP tool in a one-shot dispatch. Includes `@deep-research` / `@deep-review` agent loops with externalized state under `.opencode/specs/`.\n30: - **Parallel detached session** (use case 2) — operator already inside OpenCode (TUI / web / serve / acp) AND wants a SEPARATE session with its own session id and state directory for ablation, worker farm, or parallel research. Prompt explicitly mentions \"parallel detached\", \"ablation suite\", \"worker farm\", \"parallel research\", \"spawn detached\", or \"share URL\".\n31: - **Cross-AI orchestration handback** (use case 3) — calling AI is non-Anthropic (Codex / Copilot / Gemini), task targets a project-specific subsystem (spec-kit, memory, code-graph, advisor), and the non-Anthropic CLI cannot load the project's plugin/skill/MCP runtime on its own and needs OpenCode as a bridge.\n32: - **Agent dispatch** — task matches a specialized OpenCode agent (`general`, `context`, `orchestrate`, `write`, `review`, `debug`, `deep-research`, `deep-review`, `ultra-think`, `improve-agent`).\n33: - **Cross-repo dispatch** — session in repo A dispatches into repo B's plugin/skill/MCP runtime via `--dir <path>` or remote OpenCode server via `--attach <url>`.\n34: \n35: ### When NOT to Use\n36: \n37: - **You ARE OpenCode already.** If your runtime is OpenCode (detection signal: `$OPENCODE_CONFIG_DIR` or any `OPENCODE_*` env var set, `opencode` in process ancestry, or `~/.opencode/state/<id>/lock` present), this skill refuses to load. Self-invocation creates a circular dispatch loop and burns tokens for no value. The cli-X family is exclusively for cross-AI delegation. The single legitimate exception is an explicit \"parallel detached\" request that intentionally spawns a SEPARATE session id and state directory (use case 2); without that qualifier, the smart router refuses per ADR-001.\n38: - Simple, quick tasks where `opencode run` overhead is not worth it.\n39: - Tasks that only need a raw model dispatch — use a sibling cli-* skill.\n40: - Tasks requiring interactive TUI or web UI (use `opencode` directly instead of `opencode run`).\n41: - Context already loaded and understood by the calling AI.\n42: - Tasks where the OpenCode binary is not installed at the expected path.\n43: \n44: ---\n45: \n46: <!-- /ANCHOR:when-to-use -->\n47: <!-- ANCHOR:smart-routing -->\n48: ## 2. SMART ROUTING\n49: \n50: ### Prerequisite Detection\n51: \n52: ```bash\n53: # Verify OpenCode CLI is available\n54: command -v opencode || echo \"Not installed. Run: brew install opencode (macOS) or curl -fsSL https://opencode.ai/install | bash\"\n55: \n56: # SELF-INVOCATION GUARD (ADR-001 layered detection)\n57: # Layer 1: env var lookup — any OPENCODE_* variable\n58: env | grep -q '^OPENCODE_' && echo \"ERROR: OPENCODE_* env detected — already inside OpenCode.\"\n59: # Layer 2: process ancestry — opencode in parent tree\n60: ps -o command= -p \"$PPID\" | grep -q opencode && echo \"ERROR: opencode parent process detected.\"\n61: # Layer 3: state lock-file probe\n62: ls ~/.opencode/state/*/lock 2>/dev/null | head -1 | grep -q lock && echo \"ERROR: live OpenCode session lock detected.\"\n63: ```\n64: \n65: ### Self-Invocation Guard (ADR-001)\n66: \n67: ```python\n68: def detect_self_invocation():\n69:     \"\"\"Returns a non-None signal when the orchestrator is already running inside OpenCode.\"\"\"\n70:     # Layer 1: env var lookup — OpenCode sets OPENCODE_CONFIG_DIR and OPENCODE_* vars\n71:     for key in os.environ:\n72:         if key == 'OPENCODE_CONFIG_DIR' or key.startswith('OPENCODE_'):\n73:             return ('env', key)\n74:     # Layer 2: process ancestry — opencode in parent tree\n75:     try:\n76:         ancestry = subprocess.check_output(['ps', '-o', 'command=', '-p', str(os.getppid())]).decode()\n77:         if '/opencode' in ancestry or 'opencode ' in ancestry:\n78:             return ('ancestry', 'opencode')\n79:     except subprocess.SubprocessError:\n80:         pass\n81:     # Layer 3: state lock-file probe\n82:     state_dir = os.path.expanduser('~/.opencode/state')\n83:     if os.path.isdir(state_dir):\n84:         for entry in os.listdir(state_dir):\n85:             if os.path.exists(os.path.join(state_dir, entry, 'lock')):\n86:                 return ('lockfile', entry)\n87:     return None\n88: \n89: if detect_self_invocation():\n90:     # Single legitimate exception: explicit \"parallel detached\" keywords (use case 2)\n91:     # spawn a SEPARATE session id and state directory, not a self-dispatch.\n92:     if not has_parallel_session_keywords(prompt):\n93:         refuse(\n94:             \"Self-invocation refused: this agent is already running inside OpenCode. \"\n95:             \"Use a sibling cli-* skill or a fresh shell session in a different runtime to dispatch a different model. \"\n96:             \"For a parallel detached session, restate with explicit parallel-session keywords.\"\n97:         )\n98: ```\n99: \n100: ### Resource Loading Levels\n101: \n102: | Level       | When to Load            | Resources                      |\n103: | ----------- | ----------------------- | ------------------------------ |\n104: | ALWAYS      | Every skill invocation  | `references/cli_reference.md`, `assets/prompt_quality_card.md` |\n105: | CONDITIONAL | If intent signals match | Intent-mapped reference docs   |\n106: | ON_DEMAND   | Only on explicit request| Extended templates and patterns |\n107: \n108: ### Smart Router\n109: \n110: Provider-specific dictionaries (used by the shared helper functions in [`system-spec-kit/references/cli/shared_smart_router.md`](../system-spec-kit/references/cli/shared_smart_router.md)):\n111: \n112: ```python\n113: INTENT_SIGNALS = {\n114:     \"EXTERNAL_DISPATCH\":  {\"weight\": 4, \"keywords\": [\"delegate to opencode\", \"opencode run\", \"from claude code\", \"from codex\", \"from gemini\", \"from copilot\", \"external runtime\", \"full plugin runtime\"]},\n115:     \"PARALLEL_DETACHED\":  {\"weight\": 4, \"keywords\": [\"parallel detached\", \"ablation suite\", \"worker farm\", \"parallel research\", \"spawn detached\", \"share url\", \"share-url\", \"detached session\"]},\n116:     \"CROSS_AI_HANDBACK\":  {\"weight\": 4, \"keywords\": [\"spec kit\", \"spec-kit\", \"spec_kit\", \"code graph\", \"memory_search\", \"session_bootstrap\", \"skill advisor\", \"cross-ai handback\"]},\n117:     \"AGENT_DISPATCH\":     {\"weight\": 4, \"keywords\": [\"delegate\", \"agent\", \"deep-research\", \"deep-review\", \"ultra-think\", \"review agent\", \"context agent\"]},\n118:     \"CROSS_REPO\":         {\"weight\": 3, \"keywords\": [\"cross-repo\", \"different repo\", \"--dir\", \"another repository\", \"remote opencode\"]},\n119:     \"TEMPLATES\":          {\"weight\": 3, \"keywords\": [\"template\", \"prompt\", \"how to ask\", \"opencode prompt\"]},\n120:     \"PATTERNS\":           {\"weight\": 3, \"keywords\": [\"pattern\", \"workflow\", \"orchestrate\", \"session continue\", \"resume session\"]},\n121: }\n122: \n123: RESOURCE_MAP = {\n124:     \"EXTERNAL_DISPATCH\":  [\"references/cli_reference.md\", \"references/integration_patterns.md\"],\n125:     \"PARALLEL_DETACHED\":  [\"references/integration_patterns.md\", \"assets/prompt_templates.md\"],\n126:     \"CROSS_AI_HANDBACK\":  [\"references/integration_patterns.md\", \"references/opencode_tools.md\"],\n127:     \"AGENT_DISPATCH\":     [\"references/agent_delegation.md\", \"assets/prompt_templates.md\"],\n128:     \"CROSS_REPO\":         [\"references/cli_reference.md\", \"references/opencode_tools.md\"],\n129:     \"TEMPLATES\":          [\"assets/prompt_templates.md\", \"references/cli_reference.md\"],\n130:     \"PATTERNS\":           [\"references/integration_patterns.md\", \"references/cli_reference.md\"],\n131: }\n132: \n133: LOADING_LEVELS = {\n134:     \"ALWAYS\": [\"references/cli_reference.md\", \"assets/prompt_quality_card.md\"],\n135:     \"ON_DEMAND_KEYWORDS\": [\"full reference\", \"all templates\", \"deep dive\", \"complete guide\", \"opencode agent\", \"opencode prompt\", \"share url\", \"ablation\", \"worker farm\", \"self-invocation\", \"memory handback\"],\n136:     \"ON_DEMAND\": [\"references/opencode_tools.md\", \"assets/prompt_templates.md\"],\n137: }\n138: \n139: UNKNOWN_FALLBACK_CHECKLIST = [\n140:     \"Is the user asking about OpenCode CLI specifically?\",\n141:     \"Does the task need the project's full plugin / skill / MCP runtime?\",\n142:     \"Is a parallel detached session what they want?\",\n143:     \"Is a non-Anthropic CLI handing back to OpenCode for a spec-kit workflow?\",\n144: ]\n145: ```\n146: \n147: **Call sequence** (using shared helpers from `shared_smart_router.md`):\n148: \n149: 1. `discover_markdown_resources()` — enumerate available `.md` files under `references/` and `assets/`\n150: 2. `score_intents(task)` — keyword-weight match against `INTENT_SIGNALS`\n151: 3. `select_intents(scores, ambiguity_delta=1.0)` — top-1 or top-2 if scores within delta\n152: 4. ALWAYS-load `LOADING_LEVELS[\"ALWAYS\"]`, then UNKNOWN-fallback if max score == 0\n153: 5. CONDITIONAL-load `RESOURCE_MAP[intent]` for each selected intent\n154: 6. ON_DEMAND-load if any `ON_DEMAND_KEYWORDS` match the task text\n155: \n156: The `route_opencode_resources(task)` function body lives in [`shared_smart_router.md`](../system-spec-kit/references/cli/shared_smart_router.md) — substitute `<PROVIDER>` = `opencode`.\n157: \n158: ---\n159: \n160: <!-- /ANCHOR:smart-routing -->\n161: <!-- ANCHOR:how-it-works -->\n162: ## 3. HOW IT WORKS\n163: \n164: ### Prerequisites\n165: \n166: ```bash\n167: # Verify installation (cli-opencode v1.0.0 is pinned to opencode v1.3.17)\n168: opencode --version | grep -q '^1\\.' || echo \"Not installed or version drift. See references/cli_reference.md §9.\"\n169: \n170: # Self-invocation guard\n171: env | grep -q '^OPENCODE_' && echo \"ERROR: Already inside OpenCode session\"\n172: \n173: # Authentication — providers configured via opencode providers (alias auth)\n174: opencode providers\n175: ```\n176: \n177: **Authentication options**: `opencode auth login <provider>` for OAuth, or per-provider API key env vars (e.g. `ANTHROPIC_API_KEY`, `OPENAI_API_KEY`) read by provider plugins at session start.\n178: \n179: ### Default Invocation (Skill Default)\n180: \n181: **Default model + variant + agent + format + dir**: `opencode-go/deepseek-v4-pro` · `--variant high` · `--agent general` · `--format json` · `--dir <repo-root>`. The repo root pin avoids CWD ambiguity.\n182: \n183: ```bash\n184: opencode run \\\n185:   --model opencode-go/deepseek-v4-pro \\\n186:   --agent general \\\n187:   --variant high \\\n188:   --format json \\\n189:   --dir /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public \\\n190:   \"<prompt>\"\n191: ```\n192: \n193: **User override** (honor explicit user phrasing verbatim):\n194: \n195: | User says | Resolve to |\n196: |-----------|------------|\n197: | (nothing specified) | `--model opencode-go/deepseek-v4-pro --agent general --variant high --format json` |\n198: | \"Use anthropic claude sonnet 4-7\" | `--model anthropic/claude-sonnet-4-7 --agent general --variant high --format json` |\n199: | \"Use the deep-research agent\" | `--model opencode-go/deepseek-v4-pro --agent deep-research --variant high --format json` |\n200: | \"Use openai gpt-5.5 high\" | `--model openai/gpt-5.5 --agent general --variant high --format json` |\n201: | \"Spawn a parallel detached session on port 4096\" | (use case 2) appends `--share --port 4096` |\n202: \n203: ### Core Invocation Pattern\n204: \n205: ```bash\n206: opencode run \"prompt\" --model opencode-go/deepseek-v4-pro --agent general --variant high --format json --dir /repo 2>&1\n207: ```\n208: \n209: | Flag / Option | Purpose |\n210: |---------------|---------|\n211: | `--model <provider/model>` | Provider-prefixed model selector (e.g. `opencode-go/deepseek-v4-pro`) |\n212: | `--agent <slug>` | Agent definition from `.opencode/agent/<slug>.md` |\n213: | `--variant <level>` | Provider-specific reasoning effort (`minimal`, `low`, `medium`, `high`, `max`) |\n214: | `--format default \\| json` | Human-readable log OR newline-delimited JSON event stream |\n215: | `--dir <path>` | Working directory or remote-server path |\n216: | `-c`, `--continue` | Continue the last session in this project |\n217: | `-s`, `--session <id>` | Continue a specific session id |\n218: | `--fork` | Fork before continuing (requires `--continue` or `--session`) |\n219: | `--share` | Publish a shareable session URL — opt-in per CHK-033 |\n220: | `--port <N>` | Local server port (only for parallel detached sessions) |\n221: | `-f`, `--file <path>` | Attach file(s) to the message |\n222: | `--thinking` | Show thinking blocks |\n223: | `--pure` | Disable external plugins (debugging only) |\n224: | `--print-logs` | Stream logs to stderr |\n225: | `--log-level <level>` | DEBUG / INFO / WARN / ERROR |\n226: \n227: > **Background dispatch in a `while read` loop**: always append `</dev/null` after the redirect when backgrounding `opencode run` inside a loop. Without it the backgrounded process inherits the loop's stdin and silently consumes the rest. See `references/integration_patterns.md` §6.\n228: \n229: ### Model Selection\n230: \n231: | Provider | Model id | Reasoning effort range | Use case |\n232: |----------|----------|------------------------|----------|\n233: | opencode-go | `opencode-go/deepseek-v4-pro` (default) | `--variant` accepted; effect depends on opencode-go routing | Deep reasoning, planning, code review |\n234: | opencode-go | `opencode-go/deepseek-v4-flash` | same | Lower-tier sibling for cost/latency |\n235: | Anthropic | `anthropic/claude-opus-4-7` | `minimal`, `low`, `medium`, `high`, `max` | Available with `opencode auth login anthropic` |\n236: | OpenAI | `openai/gpt-5.4` | `minimal`, `low`, `medium`, `high`, `xhigh` | Available with openai auth |\n237: | Google | `google/gemini-2.5-pro` | `minimal`, `low`, `medium`, `high` | Available with google auth |\n238: \n239: `opencode models <provider>` enumerates available models. The skill defaults to `opencode-go/deepseek-v4-pro --variant high` because the typical task benefits from elevated reasoning.\n240: \n241: ### OpenCode Agent Delegation\n242: \n243: The calling AI is the conductor; OpenCode agents under `.opencode/agent/<slug>.md` pin the model, tool permissions, and system prompt.\n244: \n245: | Task type | Agent | Invocation pattern |\n246: |-----------|-------|---------------------|\n247: | Default / unspecified | `general` | `opencode run --agent general --variant high --format json --dir /repo \"<prompt>\"` |\n248: | Codebase exploration | `context` | `opencode run --agent context --variant high --format json --dir /repo \"Map src/\"` |\n249: | Code review | `review` | `opencode run --agent review --variant high --format json --dir /repo \"Review @src/auth.ts for security\"` |\n250: | Multi-strategy planning | `ultra-think` | `opencode run --agent ultra-think --variant high --format json --dir /repo \"Plan auth redesign\"` |\n251: | Iterative deep research | `deep-research` | `opencode run --agent deep-research --variant high --format json --dir /repo \"Iter 3 of packet 047\"` |\n252: | Iterative code review | `deep-review` | `opencode run --agent deep-review --variant high --format json --dir /repo \"Iter 5 review of packet 047\"` |\n253: | Documentation | `write` | `opencode run --agent write --variant high --format json --dir /repo \"Generate README\"` |\n254: | Multi-agent coordination | `orchestrate` | `opencode run --agent orchestrate --variant high --format json --dir /repo \"Coordinate review + tests\"` |\n255: \n256: See [agent_delegation.md](./references/agent_delegation.md) for the complete agent roster.\n257: \n258: ### Unique OpenCode Capabilities\n259: \n260: | Capability | Purpose | Invocation |\n261: |------------|---------|------------|\n262: | Full plugin / skill / MCP runtime | Dispatched session loads every project plugin, skill, MCP tool, and Spec Kit Memory | Default behavior — no special flag |\n263: | Parallel detached sessions | Spawn separate session id + state directory + optional share URL | `opencode run --share --port <N>` |\n264: | Structured event stream | Newline-delimited JSON events with stable schema | `--format json` |\n265: | Agent dispatch | Pin model + tool permissions + system prompt via slug | `--agent <slug>` |\n266: | Cross-repo dispatch | Target a different repo's runtime via path | `--dir <path>` |\n267: | Cross-server dispatch | Attach to a remote OpenCode server | `--attach <url>` |\n268: | Session continuation | Resume or fork a prior session | `-c` / `-s <id>` / `--fork` |\n269: | Plugin disable for debugging | Run without plugins | `--pure` |\n270: \n271: ### Essential Commands\n272: \n273: ```bash\n274: # 1. External runtime to OpenCode (use case 1)\n275: opencode run \\\n276:   --model opencode-go/deepseek-v4-pro --agent general --variant high --format json \\\n277:   --dir /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public \\\n278:   \"Run memory_search for 'spec kit memory health' and return top 5 results.\"\n279: \n280: # 2. Parallel detached session (use case 2 — only valid from inside OpenCode)\n281: opencode run --share --port 4096 \\\n282:   --model opencode-go/deepseek-v4-pro --agent deep-research --variant high --format json \\\n283:   --dir /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public \\\n284:   \"Run iteration 3 of the deep-research loop on packet 047.\"\n285: \n286: # 3. Cross-AI handback (use case 3 — Codex / Copilot / Gemini calling)\n287: opencode run \\\n288:   --model opencode-go/deepseek-v4-pro --agent general --variant high --format json \\\n289:   --dir /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public \\\n290:   \"Use system-spec-kit to validate packet 047. Return JSON validation report.\"\n291: \n292: # 4. Code review with the review agent\n293: opencode run \\\n294:   --model opencode-go/deepseek-v4-pro --agent review --variant high --format json \\\n295:   --dir /repo \\\n296:   \"Review @src/auth.ts for security issues. Surface P0 / P1 with file:line evidence.\"\n297: \n298: # 5. Cross-repo dispatch (Barter sibling)\n299: opencode run \\\n300:   --model opencode-go/deepseek-v4-pro --agent general --variant high --format json \\\n301:   --dir /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Barter \\\n302:   \"Draft a Level 1 spec for the auth refresh feature.\"\n303: ```\n304: \n305: ### Error Handling\n306: \n307: | Issue | Solution |\n308: |-------|----------|\n309: | `command not found: opencode` | Install via `brew install opencode` (macOS) or the standalone installer |\n310: | Self-invocation refused | Use a sibling cli-* skill OR a fresh shell session OR add explicit \"parallel detached\" keywords to the prompt |\n311: | `provider/model not found` | Run `opencode providers` to enumerate; `auth login <provider>` if needed |\n312: | `unknown option --variant` | Version drift — see `references/cli_reference.md` §9 |\n313: | Empty event stream | Pass `--format json` and parse line-delimited events |\n314: | Background dispatch hangs | Add `</dev/null` to background invocations inside `while read` loops |\n315: | `--share` URL leaks secrets | Operator MUST confirm before passing `--share` (CHK-033) |\n316: | Plugin load crash | Rerun with `--pure` to bypass plugins; surface the underlying issue |\n317: | Session never finishes | Inspect `~/.opencode/state/<session_id>/messages.jsonl` for the last tool call |\n318: \n319: ---\n320: \n321: <!-- /ANCHOR:how-it-works -->\n322: <!-- ANCHOR:rules -->\n323: ## 4. RULES\n324: \n325: ### ALWAYS\n326: \n327: 1. Verify OpenCode CLI is installed before first invocation; confirm version baseline against v1.3.17 (drift handling per `references/cli_reference.md` §9).\n328: 2. **Run the self-invocation guard before dispatch** (ADR-001): Layer 1 env-var lookup for any `OPENCODE_*`, Layer 2 process-ancestry probe for `opencode` parent, Layer 3 `~/.opencode/state/<id>/lock` probe. Trip on ANY positive — refuse unless prompt has explicit parallel-session keywords.\n329: 3. Pin model + agent + variant + format + dir explicitly. Default: `--model opencode-go/deepseek-v4-pro --agent general --variant high --format json --dir <repo-root>`. Honor user overrides verbatim.\n330: 4. Pass `--format json` unless the calling AI explicitly wants formatted output — JSON event stream is what external runtimes parse incrementally.\n331: 5. Append `</dev/null` when backgrounding `opencode run` inside `while read` loops (otherwise stdin is silently consumed).\n332: 6. **Pass the spec folder to the dispatched session** in the prompt: if the calling AI has an active Gate-3 spec folder, include `Spec folder: <path> (pre-approved, skip Gate 3)`. If none, ASK the user before delegating — the dispatched session cannot answer Gate 3 interactively in non-interactive `run` mode.\n333: 7. **Load `assets/prompt_quality_card.md` before building any dispatch prompt.** Apply the CLEAR 5-question check, tag the framework in the Bash invocation comment, and use the returned `ENHANCED_PROMPT`. If complexity ≥ 7/10 or compliance/security signals appear, dispatch `@improve-prompt` via the Task tool first.\n334: 8. Validate dispatched session output: parse JSON events incrementally (tool calls, partial messages, final summary), run syntax checks if code generated, cross-reference against project standards (sk-code-review, sk-code-opencode).\n335: 9. Capture stderr (`2>&1`) to catch tool errors and warnings.\n336: 10. Classify the use case (1 / 2 / 3) before dispatching — the smart router refuses dispatches that do not map to one of the three.\n337: \n338: ### NEVER\n339: \n340: 1. Invoke this skill from within OpenCode itself for a self-dispatch — refuse with the documented error message; use a sibling cli-* / fresh shell / parallel-session keywords.\n341: 2. Pass `--share` without operator confirmation (CHK-033) — share URL exposes session contents.\n342: 3. Trust dispatched session output blindly for security-sensitive code, send sensitive data (API keys, passwords, credentials) in prompts, or hammer the API with rapid sequential calls.\n343: 4. Use `--pure` outside of plugin debugging (disabling plugins removes the entire point of cli-opencode dispatch).\n344: 5. Nest `opencode run` inside a dispatched session's tool calls — use OpenCode's native Task tool for sub-agent dispatch.\n345: \n346: ### ESCALATE IF\n347: \n348: 1. OpenCode CLI is not installed and user has not acknowledged (provide `brew install opencode` or `curl -fsSL https://opencode.ai/install | bash`).\n349: 2. Operator wants to publish a `--share` URL — get explicit confirmation per CHK-033.\n350: 3. Binary version differs from the v1.3.17 baseline — run `opencode --version` and `opencode run --help`; surface drift and fall back or require approval.\n351: 4. Smart router cannot map the prompt to one of the three use cases — surface the disambiguation checklist from UNKNOWN_FALLBACK.\n352: 5. Self-invocation guard trips AND the prompt is ambiguous — surface the refusal with three remediation options (sibling cli-* / fresh shell / parallel-session keywords).\n353: \n354: ### Memory Handback Protocol\n355: \n356: When the calling AI needs to preserve session context from an OpenCode CLI delegation, run the canonical 7-step procedure (extract `MEMORY_HANDBACK` section → build structured JSON → scrub secrets → invoke `generate-context.js` via `--stdin`/`--json`/temp-file → `memory_index_scan`). Full procedure and caveats: [`system-spec-kit/references/cli/memory_handback.md`](../system-spec-kit/references/cli/memory_handback.md).\n357: \n358: OpenCode-specific Memory Epilogue template: see [assets/prompt_templates.md](./assets/prompt_templates.md) §14.\n359: \n360: Example invocation:\n361: ```bash\n362: printf '%s' \"$JSON_PAYLOAD\" | node .opencode/skill/system-spec-kit/scripts/dist/memory/generate-context.js --stdin [spec-folder]\n363: ```\n364: \n365: ---\n366: \n367: <!-- /ANCHOR:rules -->\n368: <!-- ANCHOR:references -->\n369: ## 5. REFERENCES\n370: \n371: ### Core References\n372: \n373: - [cli_reference.md](./references/cli_reference.md) - Full subcommand and flag reference, models, version drift handling\n374: - [integration_patterns.md](./references/integration_patterns.md) - 3 use cases, decision tree, self-invocation guard, silent stdin\n375: - [opencode_tools.md](./references/opencode_tools.md) - Unique value props vs sibling cli-* skills\n376: - [agent_delegation.md](./references/agent_delegation.md) - Agent routing matrix, leaf-agent constraints\n377: \n378: ### Templates and Assets\n379: \n380: - [prompt_templates.md](./assets/prompt_templates.md) - 13 numbered copy-paste templates per use case + agent + handback\n381: - [prompt_quality_card.md](./assets/prompt_quality_card.md) - Framework selection, CLEAR 5-check, escalation triggers\n382: \n383: ### Shared (cli-* family)\n384: - [shared_smart_router.md](../system-spec-kit/references/cli/shared_smart_router.md) - Helper-function bodies for the smart router.\n385: - [memory_handback.md](../system-spec-kit/references/cli/memory_handback.md) - Canonical 7-step Memory Handback procedure.\n386: \n387: ### External\n388: - [OpenCode GitHub](https://github.com/sst/opencode) - Official repository\n389: - [OpenCode Install](https://opencode.ai/install) - Standalone installer entry point\n390: - [OpenCode Documentation](https://opencode.ai/docs) - Official docs\n391: \n392: ### Reference Loading Notes\n393: \n394: - Load only references needed for current intent.\n395: - Smart Routing (Section 2) is the single routing authority.\n396: - `cli_reference.md` and `prompt_quality_card.md` are ALWAYS loaded as baseline.\n397: \n398: ---\n399: \n400: <!-- /ANCHOR:references -->\n401: <!-- ANCHOR:success-criteria -->\n402: ## 6. SUCCESS CRITERIA\n403: \n404: ### Task Completion\n405: \n406: - OpenCode CLI invoked with the correct subcommand, flags, model, agent, variant, format, and dir.\n407: - Self-invocation guard checked before dispatch — refused when appropriate.\n408: - Use case (1 / 2 / 3) classified explicitly before invocation.\n409: - JSON event stream captured, parsed incrementally, validated, integrated.\n410: - No security vulnerabilities introduced from generated code.\n411: - `--share` URLs opt-in with operator confirmation per CHK-033.\n412: - Background dispatches in `while read` loops include `</dev/null` redirect.\n413: - Memory Handback extracted and saved through `generate-context.js` when applicable.\n414: \n415: ### Skill Quality\n416: \n417: - All 8 sections present with proper anchor comments.\n418: - Smart routing covers all intent signals with UNKNOWN_FALLBACK.\n419: - Reference files provide deep-dive content without duplication.\n420: - Self-invocation guard pseudocode reproduced in Section 2 mirrors ADR-001.\n421: \n422: ---\n423: \n424: <!-- /ANCHOR:success-criteria -->\n425: <!-- ANCHOR:integration-points -->\n426: ## 7. INTEGRATION POINTS\n427: \n428: ### Framework Integration\n429: \n430: This skill operates within the behavioral framework defined in [AGENTS.md](../../../AGENTS.md).\n431: \n432: Key integrations:\n433: - **Gate 2**: Skill routing via the Skill Advisor Hook (or `skill_advisor.py` fallback)\n434: - **Tool Routing**: Per AGENTS.md Section 6 decision tree\n435: - **Memory**: Context preserved via Spec Kit Memory MCP (`generate-context.js`)\n436: - **Validation**: `bash .opencode/skill/system-spec-kit/scripts/spec/validate.sh` for spec-folder workflows\n437: \n438: **Tool roles**: Bash dispatches the CLI; Read/Glob/Grep validate output and probe `~/.opencode/state/` for session locks.\n439: \n440: ### Related Skills\n441: \n442: | Skill | Integration |\n443: |-------|-------------|\n444: | **cli-claude-code** | Sibling — dispatch raw Claude when full project runtime is not needed |\n445: | **cli-codex** | Sibling — dispatch Codex for code generation; cli-opencode is the bridge for spec-kit handback |\n446: | **cli-copilot** | Sibling — dispatch Copilot for cloud-agent style execution |\n447: | **cli-gemini** | Sibling — dispatch Gemini for Google Search grounding |\n448: | **system-spec-kit** | Cross-AI handback target — dispatched sessions load this skill for spec-folder workflows |\n449: | **sk-doc** | Doc generation in dispatched `@write` agent runs |\n450: | **sk-code-opencode** | Code-quality enforcement in dispatched code review or generation runs |\n451: | **sk-deep-research** | LEAF agent dispatched as `--agent deep-research` for parallel research iterations |\n452: | **sk-deep-review** | LEAF agent dispatched as `--agent deep-review` for parallel review iterations |\n453: | **mcp-code-mode** | Code Mode tools available inside the dispatched session via the project's MCP wiring |\n454: \n455: ---\n456: \n457: <!-- /ANCHOR:integration-points -->\n458: <!-- ANCHOR:related-resources -->\n459: ## 8. RELATED RESOURCES\n460: \n461: See Section 5 REFERENCES for the canonical reference, asset, shared, and external link list.\n462: \n463: ---\n464: \n465: <!-- /ANCHOR:related-resources -->\n\n(End of file - total 465 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\nname: cli-opencode\ndescription: \"OpenCode CLI orchestrator covering three use cases: external AI runtimes dispatching opencode run, in-OpenCode parallel detached sessions for ablation and worker farms, and cross-AI orchestration handback with full plugin, skill, and MCP runtime context.\"\nallowed-tools: [Bash, Read, Glob, Grep]\nversion: 1.0.0\n---\n\n<!-- Keywords: opencode, opencode-cli, opencode-run, cross-ai, spec-kit-runtime, plugin-runtime, parallel-sessions, share-url, detached-session, agent-delegation, anthropic, openai, google, gemini -->\n\n# OpenCode CLI Orchestrator - Full-Runtime Cross-AI Dispatch\n\n> **CRITICAL — SELF-INVOCATION PROHIBITED**\n>\n> This skill dispatches to the OpenCode CLI binary (`opencode`). If the agent currently reading this skill is itself running inside OpenCode (TUI / acp / serve / run modes — detection signals listed in §2), the skill MUST refuse to load and return the documented error message instead of generating any `opencode` invocation. The only exception is an explicit \"parallel detached\" request that intentionally spawns a SEPARATE session with its own session id and state directory.\n>\n> Just as a Claude Code agent never calls cli-claude-code, an OpenCode agent never calls cli-opencode, a Codex agent never calls cli-codex, a Copilot agent never calls cli-copilot, and a Gemini agent never calls cli-gemini. The cli-X skills are for **cross-AI delegation only** — never self-invocation.\n\nOrchestrate OpenCode's `opencode run` from external AI assistants (Claude Code, Codex, Copilot, Gemini, raw shell) AND from inside an existing OpenCode session for parallel detached workers. Three documented use cases keep the cycle risk explicit while giving every dispatch path a copy-paste invocation shape.\n\n**Core Principle**: The calling AI stays the conductor. Delegate to OpenCode for what it does best — full plugin, skill, MCP, and Spec Kit Memory runtime in a one-shot dispatch. Validate and integrate the output.","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":".opencode/skill/cli-opencode/SKILL.md","time":{"start":1777215862975,"end":1777215862996}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1777215864565,"sessionID":"ses_235ae4ddfffeslQpORMPty8nFN","part":{"id":"prt_dca51f9bf001xWjrQECvr6gIR3","messageID":"msg_dca51e361002ZFnqukUhAmnxYz","sessionID":"ses_235ae4ddfffeslQpORMPty8nFN","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_01_CB76eMLspXF32Ki1x9fBhy9c","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skill/cli-opencode/README.md"},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skill/cli-opencode/README.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: title: \"OpenCode CLI Orchestrator\"\n3: description: \"Cross-AI task delegation and parallel detached sessions for OpenCode CLI with full plugin, skill, and MCP runtime context. Three documented use cases plus a layered self-invocation guard.\"\n4: trigger_phrases:\n5:   - \"opencode cli\"\n6:   - \"opencode run\"\n7:   - \"delegate to opencode\"\n8:   - \"parallel detached session\"\n9:   - \"spec kit runtime\"\n10: ---\n11: \n12: # OpenCode CLI Orchestrator\n13: \n14: > Delegate tasks from any AI assistant to OpenCode CLI for one-shot dispatches into the project's full plugin, skill, and MCP runtime, plus parallel detached sessions for ablation, worker farms, and parallel research.\n15: \n16: ---\n17: \n18: <!-- ANCHOR:table-of-contents -->\n19: ## TABLE OF CONTENTS\n20: \n21: - [1. OVERVIEW](#1-overview)\n22: - [2. QUICK START](#2-quick-start)\n23: - [3. FEATURES](#3-features)\n24:   - [3.1 FEATURE HIGHLIGHTS](#31-feature-highlights)\n25:   - [3.2 FEATURE REFERENCE](#32-feature-reference)\n26: - [4. STRUCTURE](#4-structure)\n27: - [5. CONFIGURATION](#5-configuration)\n28: - [6. USAGE EXAMPLES](#6-usage-examples)\n29: - [7. TROUBLESHOOTING](#7-troubleshooting)\n30: - [8. FAQ](#8-faq)\n31: - [9. RELATED DOCUMENTS](#9-related-documents)\n32: \n33: <!-- /ANCHOR:table-of-contents -->\n34: \n35: ---\n36: \n37: <!-- ANCHOR:overview -->\n38: ## 1. OVERVIEW\n39: \n40: ### What This Skill Does\n41: \n42: This skill lets external AI assistants (Claude Code, Codex, Copilot, Gemini, raw shell) invoke OpenCode CLI as a one-shot specialist tool. The calling AI stays the conductor, delegating specific tasks to OpenCode and integrating the structured event stream back into its own workflow.\n43: \n44: OpenCode brings a capability that the four sibling cli-* skills do not: a one-shot dispatch that loads the full plugin, skill, MCP, and Spec Kit Memory runtime. When `opencode run` starts a session, every plugin in the project's `opencode.json` loads, every skill under `.opencode/skill/` becomes accessible, every MCP tool wired through the project becomes callable, and the Spec Kit Memory database is on-line.\n45: \n46: The skill documents three orthogonal use cases: external runtime to OpenCode, in-OpenCode parallel detached sessions for ablation and worker farms, and cross-AI handback where a non-Anthropic CLI needs OpenCode-specific plugins.\n47: \n48: The skill includes a layered self-invocation guard. Three checks (env var lookup, process ancestry, lock-file probe) detect when the orchestrator is already running inside OpenCode. The smart router refuses self-dispatch with a documented error message that names the remediation path.\n49: \n50: ### Key Statistics\n51: \n52: | Category | Value | Details |\n53: |----------|-------|---------|\n54: | **Use cases** | 3 | External runtime, in-OpenCode parallel detached, cross-AI handback |\n55: | **Self-invocation layers** | 3 | Env var, process ancestry, lock-file probe |\n56: | **Default invocation** | `--model opencode-go/deepseek-v4-pro --agent general --variant high --format json` | Pinned shape for routine dispatches |\n57: | **References** | 4 | cli_reference, integration_patterns, opencode_tools, agent_delegation |\n58: | **Assets** | 2 | prompt_quality_card, prompt_templates (13 templates) |\n59: | **Version baseline** | opencode v1.3.17 | Pinned in cli_reference §9 |\n60: | **Skill version** | 1.0.0 | Initial release |\n61: \n62: ### How This Compares\n63: \n64: | Capability | Claude Code CLI | Codex CLI | Copilot CLI | Gemini CLI | OpenCode CLI |\n65: |------------|-----------------|-----------|-------------|------------|--------------|\n66: | **Plugin runtime** | None (raw Claude) | None (raw Codex) | Limited | None | Full project plugins |\n67: | **Skill runtime** | Native via SKILL.md inside Claude Code only | None | None | None | Full project skills |\n68: | **MCP runtime** | None (per-session config) | Native via `codex mcp` | Limited | None | Full project MCP servers |\n69: | **Spec Kit Memory** | None (no project-aware DB) | None | None | None | Full project DB |\n70: | **Parallel detached sessions** | No | Session fork | Cloud delegation | No | `--share --port N` |\n71: | **Agent dispatch** | `--agent` (Claude agents) | `-p` profile | Built-in | None | `--agent` (project agents) |\n72: | **Cross-repo dispatch** | No | No | Cloud only | No | `--dir <path>` |\n73: \n74: ### Key Features at a Glance\n75: \n76: | Feature | What It Does |\n77: |---------|-------------|\n78: | **Full plugin runtime** | Dispatched session loads every project plugin from `opencode.json` |\n79: | **Full skill runtime** | All skills under `.opencode/skill/` become accessible inside the dispatched session |\n80: | **Full MCP runtime** | Spec Kit Memory's 40+ tools, CocoIndex semantic search, Code Mode, sequential thinking — all callable |\n81: | **Parallel detached sessions** | `--share --port N` spawns a separate session id with independent state |\n82: | **Structured event stream** | `--format json` emits typed JSON events the calling AI parses incrementally |\n83: | **Agent dispatch** | `--agent <slug>` loads project agents (deep-research, deep-review, review, ultra-think, etc.) |\n84: | **Cross-repo dispatch** | `--dir <path>` targets a different repo's plugin / skill / MCP runtime |\n85: | **Self-invocation guard** | Three-layer detection refuses circular dispatch when already inside OpenCode |\n86: | **Memory handback** | `MEMORY_HANDBACK` delimiters preserve session context through `generate-context.js` |\n87: \n88: ### Requirements\n89: \n90: | Requirement | Value | Notes |\n91: |-------------|-------|-------|\n92: | **CLI** | OpenCode v1.3.17+ | `brew install opencode` (macOS) or `curl -fsSL https://opencode.ai/install \\| bash` |\n93: | **Auth** | Per-provider (`opencode auth login <provider>`) or env vars | `ANTHROPIC_API_KEY`, `OPENAI_API_KEY`, etc. |\n94: | **Node.js** | 18+ | Required for the npm install path |\n95: \n96: <!-- /ANCHOR:overview -->\n97: \n98: ---\n99: \n100: <!-- ANCHOR:quick-start -->\n101: ## 2. QUICK START\n102: \n103: ### 1. Verify Installation\n104: \n105: ```bash\n106: command -v opencode || echo \"Not installed. Run: brew install opencode (macOS) or curl -fsSL https://opencode.ai/install | bash\"\n107: opencode --version\n108: ```\n109: \n110: ### 2. Run the Self-Invocation Guard\n111: \n112: ```bash\n113: # If any of these print, you are inside OpenCode and must use a sibling cli-* skill instead\n114: env | grep -q '^OPENCODE_' && echo \"OPENCODE_* env detected\"\n115: ps -o command= -p \"$PPID\" | grep -q opencode && echo \"opencode parent process\"\n116: ls ~/.opencode/state/*/lock 2>/dev/null | head -1 | grep -q lock && echo \"live OpenCode session lock\"\n117: ```\n118: \n119: ### 3. Run a Simple External-Runtime Dispatch\n120: \n121: ```bash\n122: opencode run \\\n123:   --model opencode-go/deepseek-v4-pro \\\n124:   --agent general \\\n125:   --variant high \\\n126:   --format json \\\n127:   --dir /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public \\\n128:   \"Use memory_search to find context on packet 047.\" 2>&1\n129: ```\n130: \n131: ### 4. Spawn a Parallel Detached Session\n132: \n133: ```bash\n134: opencode run --share --port 4096 \\\n135:   --model opencode-go/deepseek-v4-pro \\\n136:   --agent deep-research \\\n137:   --variant high \\\n138:   --format json \\\n139:   --dir /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public \\\n140:   \"Run iteration 3 of the deep-research loop on packet 047.\" 2>&1\n141: ```\n142: \n143: <!-- /ANCHOR:quick-start -->\n144: \n145: ---\n146: \n147: <!-- ANCHOR:features -->\n148: ## 3. FEATURES\n149: \n150: ### 3.1 FEATURE HIGHLIGHTS\n151: \n152: OpenCode CLI stands apart from the four sibling cli-* skills in three ways: full project runtime, parallel detached sessions, and cross-repo dispatch.\n153: \n154: The full project runtime is the headline capability. Sibling cli-* dispatches send a raw model behind a thin CLI wrapper. The dispatched call loads no plugins, no skills, no MCP tools, no Spec Kit Memory. `opencode run` is different. The dispatched session loads every plugin in `opencode.json`, every skill under `.opencode/skill/`, every MCP server wired through the project, and the Spec Kit Memory database. A one-shot dispatch becomes a fully-loaded project agent.\n155: \n156: Parallel detached sessions matter for ablation suites, worker farms, and parallel research. `opencode run --share --port N` spawns a separate session id with its own state directory under `~/.opencode/state/<session_id>/`. The original session continues unaffected. The new session can publish a `--share` URL for browser inspection. This pattern is unique to cli-opencode because the four sibling binaries do not have an equivalent of OpenCode's session model.\n157: \n158: Cross-repo dispatch via `--dir <path>` lets a session in repo A target repo B's plugin / skill / MCP runtime. Combined with `--attach <url>`, it can reach a remote OpenCode server. The four siblings have no equivalent — their CWD is wherever the calling AI lives.\n159: \n160: The skill is built around a self-invocation guard that protects against circular dispatch. Three layers of detection (env var lookup, process ancestry probe, lock-file check) trip when the orchestrator is already running inside OpenCode. The smart router then refuses unless the prompt explicitly names a parallel detached session.\n161: \n162: ### 3.2 FEATURE REFERENCE\n163: \n164: #### Use Cases\n165: \n166: | Use case | Calling runtime | Target | Self-invocation? |\n167: |----------|-----------------|--------|------------------|\n168: | **External runtime to OpenCode** | Claude Code, Codex, Copilot, Gemini, raw shell | OpenCode for full plugin / skill / MCP runtime | No |\n169: | **In-OpenCode parallel detached** | OpenCode itself (TUI / web / serve / acp) | New OpenCode session via `--share --port N` | No (different session id) |\n170: | **Cross-AI orchestration handback** | Codex / Copilot / Gemini | OpenCode for spec-kit specific workflows | No |\n171: \n172: #### Models\n173: \n174: | Provider | Model id | Variant range | Default for cli-opencode? |\n175: |----------|----------|---------------|---------------------------|\n176: | opencode-go | `opencode-go/deepseek-v4-pro` | provider-specific (variant flag accepted; effect depends on opencode-go routing) | YES |\n177: | opencode-go | `opencode-go/deepseek-v4-flash` | same | No (lower-tier sibling for cost/latency) |\n178: | Anthropic | `anthropic/claude-opus-4-7` | minimal / low / medium / high / max | No (requires `opencode auth login anthropic`) |\n179: | OpenAI | `openai/gpt-5.4` | minimal / low / medium / high / xhigh | No (requires openai auth) |\n180: | Google | `google/gemini-2.5-pro` | minimal / low / medium / high | No (requires google auth) |\n181: \n182: #### Core Flags\n183: \n184: | Flag | Short | Purpose |\n185: |------|-------|---------|\n186: | `--model` | `-m` | Provider-prefixed model selector |\n187: | `--agent` | | Project agent slug |\n188: | `--variant` | | Provider-specific reasoning effort |\n189: | `--format` | | `default` (formatted) or `json` (event stream) |\n190: | `--dir` | | Working directory or remote-server path |\n191: | `--share` | | Publish session share URL (operator confirmation required) |\n192: | `--port` | | Local server port for parallel detached sessions |\n193: | `--continue` | `-c` | Continue last session in this project |\n194: | `--session` | `-s` | Continue specific session id |\n195: | `--fork` | | Fork before continuing (requires `--continue` or `--session`) |\n196: | `--file` | `-f` | Attach files to message |\n197: | `--thinking` | | Show thinking blocks |\n198: | `--pure` | | Disable plugins (debugging only) |\n199: \n200: #### Agent Roster\n201: \n202: | Agent | Purpose | Constraint |\n203: |-------|---------|------------|\n204: | `general` | Default subagent | None |\n205: | `context` | Codebase exploration | LEAF — read-only, no sub-dispatches |\n206: | `orchestrate` | Multi-agent coordination | None |\n207: | `write` | Documentation generation | None |\n208: | `review` | Code review | READ-ONLY |\n209: | `debug` | Fresh-perspective debugging | Exclusive write access for `debug-delegation.md` |\n210: | `deep-research` | Iterative research loop | LEAF — single iteration |\n211: | `deep-review` | Iterative code review loop | LEAF — single iteration |\n212: | `ultra-think` | Multi-strategy planning | PLANNING-ONLY |\n213: | `improve-agent` | Agent improvement proposals | Proposal-only |\n214: \n215: <!-- /ANCHOR:features -->\n216: \n217: ---\n218: \n219: <!-- ANCHOR:structure -->\n220: ## 4. STRUCTURE\n221: \n222: ```text\n223: cli-opencode/\n224:   SKILL.md                              # Skill definition, smart routing, self-invocation guard\n225:   README.md                             # This file\n226:   graph-metadata.json                   # Sibling edges, intent signals, derived block\n227:   assets/\n228:     prompt_quality_card.md              # Framework selection, CLEAR 5-check\n229:     prompt_templates.md                 # 13 copy-paste templates per use case + agent + handback\n230:   references/\n231:     cli_reference.md                    # Subcommands, flags, models, version drift\n232:     integration_patterns.md             # 3 use cases, decision tree, self-invocation guard\n233:     opencode_tools.md                   # Unique value props vs sibling cli-* skills\n234:     agent_delegation.md                 # Agent routing matrix, leaf-agent constraints\n235: ```\n236: \n237: <!-- /ANCHOR:structure -->\n238: \n239: ---\n240: \n241: <!-- ANCHOR:configuration -->\n242: ## 5. CONFIGURATION\n243: \n244: ### Authentication\n245: \n246: OpenCode resolves credentials through configured providers. Use `opencode providers` (alias `auth`) to enumerate.\n247: \n248: | Method | Setup | Best For |\n249: |--------|-------|----------|\n250: | **OAuth via providers** | `opencode auth login <provider>` | Interactive browser flow |\n251: | **Per-provider env vars** | `export ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=...` | Programmatic / CI use |\n252: | **Credential file** | Per-provider config under `~/.opencode/auth/` | Persistent setups |\n253: \n254: ### Model Defaults\n255: \n256: cli-opencode defaults to `opencode-go/deepseek-v4-pro --variant high` for cross-AI dispatches because routine cli-opencode tasks benefit from elevated reasoning. Override per invocation:\n257: \n258: ```bash\n259: opencode run \\\n260:   --model openai/gpt-5.5 \\\n261:   --variant high \\\n262:   --agent general \\\n263:   --format json \\\n264:   --dir /repo \\\n265:   \"<prompt>\"\n266: ```\n267: \n268: ### Session Modes\n269: \n270: | Mode | Behavior | Use Case |\n271: |------|----------|----------|\n272: | One-shot (default) | Single dispatch, session terminates after response | Most cli-opencode dispatches |\n273: | `-c` / `--continue` | Continue the last session in this project | Memory-threaded continuation |\n274: | `-s <id>` / `--session <id>` | Continue a specific session | Resume by id |\n275: | `--fork` | Branch from a continued session | Diverge from a known prior state |\n276: | `--share --port N` | Detached session with publishable URL | Use case 2 (parallel research) |\n277: \n278: <!-- /ANCHOR:configuration -->\n279: \n280: ---\n281: \n282: <!-- ANCHOR:usage-examples -->\n283: ## 6. USAGE EXAMPLES\n284: \n285: ### External Runtime to OpenCode (Use Case 1)\n286: \n287: ```bash\n288: opencode run \\\n289:   --model opencode-go/deepseek-v4-pro \\\n290:   --agent general \\\n291:   --variant high \\\n292:   --format json \\\n293:   --dir /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public \\\n294:   \"Search Spec Kit Memory for context on packet 047. Return top 5 hits as JSON.\" 2>&1\n295: ```\n296: \n297: ### Parallel Detached Session (Use Case 2)\n298: \n299: ```bash\n300: opencode run --share --port 4096 \\\n301:   --model opencode-go/deepseek-v4-pro \\\n302:   --agent deep-research \\\n303:   --variant high \\\n304:   --format json \\\n305:   --dir /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public \\\n306:   \"Run iteration 3 of the deep-research loop on packet 047. Externalize state to scratch/iteration-3.jsonl.\" 2>&1\n307: ```\n308: \n309: ### Cross-AI Handback (Use Case 3)\n310: \n311: ```bash\n312: # Calling AI is Codex / Copilot / Gemini — needs OpenCode for spec-kit workflow\n313: opencode run \\\n314:   --model opencode-go/deepseek-v4-pro \\\n315:   --agent general \\\n316:   --variant high \\\n317:   --format json \\\n318:   --dir /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public \\\n319:   \"Use system-spec-kit to validate packet 047. Return strict-mode validation report as JSON.\" 2>&1\n320: ```\n321: \n322: ### Code Review with the Review Agent\n323: \n324: ```bash\n325: opencode run \\\n326:   --model opencode-go/deepseek-v4-pro \\\n327:   --agent review \\\n328:   --variant high \\\n329:   --format json \\\n330:   --dir /repo \\\n331:   \"Review @src/auth.ts for security issues. Surface P0 / P1 findings with file:line evidence.\" 2>&1\n332: ```\n333: \n334: ### Worker Farm (Background Loop with `</dev/null`)\n335: \n336: ```bash\n337: for n in $(seq 1 8); do\n338:   port=$((4100 + n))\n339:   opencode run --share --port \"$port\" \\\n340:     --model opencode-go/deepseek-v4-pro \\\n341:     --agent general \\\n342:     --variant high \\\n343:     --format json \\\n344:     --dir /repo \\\n345:     \"Worker $n: <shard-specific prompt>\" > \"logs/worker-$n.log\" 2>&1 </dev/null &\n346: done\n347: wait\n348: ```\n349: \n350: <!-- /ANCHOR:usage-examples -->\n351: \n352: ---\n353: \n354: <!-- ANCHOR:troubleshooting -->\n355: ## 7. TROUBLESHOOTING\n356: \n357: ### OpenCode CLI Not Found\n358: \n359: **What you see**: `command not found: opencode`\n360: **Common causes**: Binary not on PATH or not installed.\n361: **Fix**: Run `brew install opencode` (macOS) or `curl -fsSL https://opencode.ai/install | bash`. Verify with `command -v opencode`.\n362: \n363: ### Self-Invocation Refused\n364: \n365: **What you see**: `ERROR: cli-opencode self-invocation refused. You are already inside OpenCode...`\n366: **Common causes**: The smart router detected an `OPENCODE_*` env var, an `opencode` parent process, or a live `~/.opencode/state/<id>/lock`.\n367: **Fix**: Use a sibling cli-* skill (cli-claude-code, cli-codex, cli-copilot, cli-gemini) OR open a fresh shell session OR add explicit \"parallel detached\" / \"ablation suite\" / \"worker farm\" / \"share URL\" keywords to the prompt to switch the router into use case 2.\n368: \n369: ### Authentication Failure\n370: \n371: **What you see**: `provider/model not found` or `401 Unauthorized`\n372: **Common causes**: Provider not configured or credentials expired.\n373: **Fix**: Run `opencode providers` to enumerate. Re-authenticate with `opencode auth login <provider>`.\n374: \n375: ### Background Dispatch Hangs\n376: \n377: **What you see**: A backgrounded `opencode run` inside a `while read` loop runs once and the loop exits early.\n378: **Common causes**: The backgrounded process inherits the loop's stdin and silently consumes the rest.\n379: **Fix**: Add `</dev/null` after the redirect: `opencode run ... > log.out 2>&1 </dev/null &`. See `references/integration_patterns.md` §6.\n380: \n381: ### Plugin Load Crash\n382: \n383: **What you see**: `MODULE_NOT_FOUND` or plugin-loader stack trace at session start.\n384: **Common causes**: A plugin path is wrong or a dependency is missing.\n385: **Fix**: Rerun with `--pure` to bypass plugins. The dispatched session will not have full project runtime — surface the underlying issue as a separate task.\n386: \n387: ### Version Drift\n388: \n389: **What you see**: `unknown option --variant` or `unknown option --share`.\n390: **Common causes**: Binary is older than the v1.3.17 baseline.\n391: **Fix**: Run `opencode --version` and `opencode run --help`. Compare against `references/cli_reference.md` §9 (Version Drift). Either upgrade the binary or fall back to the closest analogue flag.\n392: \n393: <!-- /ANCHOR:troubleshooting -->\n394: \n395: ---\n396: \n397: <!-- ANCHOR:faq -->\n398: ## 8. FAQ\n399: \n400: ### General\n401: \n402: **Q: When should I use OpenCode CLI instead of the four siblings?**\n403: A: Use cli-opencode when the task needs the project's full plugin / skill / MCP / Spec Kit Memory runtime, when you want a parallel detached session for ablation or worker farms, or when a non-Anthropic CLI needs OpenCode-specific plugins. For raw model dispatches, use the appropriate sibling.\n404: \n405: **Q: Can OpenCode CLI search the web?**\n406: A: Indirectly — the dispatched session can call Code Mode (mcp-code-mode) to reach Webflow / ClickUp / Figma / Chrome DevTools, or call CocoIndex for semantic code search, but there is no first-class `--search` flag. For Google Search grounding use cli-gemini; for Codex's `--search` use cli-codex.\n407: \n408: **Q: How does the self-invocation guard work?**\n409: A: Three layers (per ADR-001). Layer 1 checks for any `OPENCODE_*` env var. Layer 2 walks the process ancestry looking for `opencode`. Layer 3 probes `~/.opencode/state/<id>/lock`. ANY positive trips the guard. The router then refuses unless the prompt has explicit parallel-session keywords.\n410: \n411: ### Models\n412: \n413: **Q: Which model should I default to?**\n414: A: `opencode-go/deepseek-v4-pro` with `--variant high`. cli-opencode dispatches typically benefit from elevated reasoning because the dispatched session has full project context.\n415: \n416: **Q: Can I use OpenAI or Google models?**\n417: A: Yes — pass `--model openai/gpt-5.5` or `--model google/gemini-2.5-pro`. Run `opencode models <provider>` to enumerate.\n418: \n419: ### Sessions\n420: \n421: **Q: How do I share a session URL?**\n422: A: Pass `--share` and an explicit `--port`. The URL exposes session contents, so the calling AI MUST get operator confirmation before publishing per CHK-033.\n423: \n424: **Q: What is the difference between `--continue`, `--session <id>`, and `--fork`?**\n425: A: `--continue` resumes the last session in the project. `--session <id>` resumes a specific id. `--fork` (used with `--continue` or `--session`) branches a new session from the resumed state.\n426: \n427: ### Agents\n428: \n429: **Q: How do I pick the right agent?**\n430: A: Match the task type to the agent roster in Section 3.2. For routine work, use `general`. For research loops, `deep-research`. For code review, `review`. For multi-strategy planning, `ultra-think`.\n431: \n432: **Q: Can the dispatched session spawn its own sub-agents?**\n433: A: Yes via the dispatched session's native Task tool — but NOT via nested `opencode run` invocations. Nested CLI calls break the orchestration tree. Use `--agent orchestrate` for the entry-point dispatch and let the orchestrator handle sub-agent dispatch internally.\n434: \n435: <!-- /ANCHOR:faq -->\n436: \n437: ---\n438: \n439: <!-- ANCHOR:related-documents -->\n440: ## 9. RELATED DOCUMENTS\n441: \n442: ### Skill Resources\n443: - [SKILL.md](./SKILL.md): Skill definition, smart routing logic, self-invocation guard\n444: - [cli_reference.md](./references/cli_reference.md): Subcommands, flags, models, version drift\n445: - [integration_patterns.md](./references/integration_patterns.md): 3 use cases, decision tree, self-invocation guard\n446: - [opencode_tools.md](./references/opencode_tools.md): Unique capabilities and cross-CLI comparison\n447: - [agent_delegation.md](./references/agent_delegation.md): Agent roster, routing matrix, leaf constraints\n448: - [prompt_templates.md](./assets/prompt_templates.md): 13 copy-paste templates\n449: - [prompt_quality_card.md](./assets/prompt_quality_card.md): Framework selection, CLEAR 5-check\n450: \n451: ### Related Skills\n452: - [cli-claude-code](../cli-claude-code/): Anthropic Claude Code CLI orchestrator\n453: - [cli-codex](../cli-codex/): OpenAI Codex CLI orchestrator\n454: - [cli-copilot](../cli-copilot/): GitHub Copilot CLI orchestrator\n455: - [cli-gemini](../cli-gemini/): Google Gemini CLI orchestrator\n456: - [system-spec-kit](../system-spec-kit/): Spec folder workflow + Spec Kit Memory (cross-AI handback target)\n457: \n458: <!-- /ANCHOR:related-documents -->\n\n(End of file - total 458 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\ntitle: \"OpenCode CLI Orchestrator\"\ndescription: \"Cross-AI task delegation and parallel detached sessions for OpenCode CLI with full plugin, skill, and MCP runtime context. Three documented use cases plus a layered self-invocation guard.\"\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"opencode cli\"\n  - \"opencode run\"\n  - \"delegate to opencode\"\n  - \"parallel detached session\"\n  - \"spec kit runtime\"\n---\n\n# OpenCode CLI Orchestrator\n\n> Delegate tasks from any AI assistant to OpenCode CLI for one-shot dispatches into the project's full plugin, skill, and MCP runtime, plus parallel detached sessions for ablation, worker farms, and parallel research.\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:table-of-contents -->\n## TABLE OF CONTENTS\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":".opencode/skill/cli-opencode/README.md","time":{"start":1777215864546,"end":1777215864562}}}}
