{"type":"text","timestamp":1777215943382,"sessionID":"ses_235ae4ddfffeslQpORMPty8nFN","part":{"id":"prt_dca527fef001YcXDaqly2JFk4K","messageID":"msg_dca5273e0001Q7WJJbf2o72Qe9","sessionID":"ses_235ae4ddfffeslQpORMPty8nFN","type":"text","text":"Here is the architecture analysis:\n\n---\n\n## Architecture of `.opencode/skill/cli-opencode/`\n\n### Entry Points\n\n| File | Role |\n|---|---|\n| **`SKILL.md`** | Primary entry point. Loaded by the Skill tool when Gate 2 routes to `cli-opencode`. Contains the full workflow: smart routing (§2), invocation shapes (§3), rules (§4), and the self-invocation guard (ADR-001). |\n| **`README.md`** | Human-facing mirror. No runtime behavior; serves as a readable reference with feature catalog, FAQ, and structure map. |\n| **`graph-metadata.json`** | Machine-readable skill graph descriptor. Declares the skill's `family: cli`, sibling edges to the four peer cli-* skills (weight 0.5 each), domains, intent signals, and derived trigger phrases. Consumed by the Skill Advisor and Spec Kit Memory's indexer. |\n\n### Key Modules (references/ and assets/)\n\n**References/** (4 docs — loaded conditionally via the smart router's `RESOURCE_MAP`):\n\n| File | Intent mapping | Content |\n|---|---|---|\n| `cli_reference.md` | ALWAYS loaded | 295-line subcommand/flag/model reference pinned to OpenCode v1.3.17. Covers `run`, `serve`, `attach`, `agent`, `debug`, etc. |\n| `integration_patterns.md` | `EXTERNAL_DISPATCH`, `PARALLEL_DETACHED`, `CROSS_AI_HANDBACK`, `PATTERNS` | The 3 use cases (per ADR-002), self-invocation guard decision tree (ADR-001), background dispatch `< /dev/null` rule, and copy-paste invocation shapes. |\n| `opencode_tools.md` | `CROSS_AI_HANDBACK`, `CROSS_REPO` | Unique capabilities comparison: full plugin/skill/MCP runtime, parallel detached sessions, structured event stream, cross-repo dispatch. Positions `opencode run` against the four sibling cli-* dispatches. |\n| `agent_delegation.md` | `AGENT_DISPATCH` | 445-line agent routing matrix. Documents `--agent <slug>` resolution from `.opencode/agent/<slug>.md`, the conductor/executor orchestration model, LEAF agent constraints, and per-agent invocation patterns. |\n\n**Assets/** (2 docs):\n\n| File | Loading level | Content |\n|---|---|---|\n| `prompt_quality_card.md` | ALWAYS | Framework selection table (RCAF/COSTAR/RACE/CIDI/TIDD-EC/CRISPE/CRAFT) + CLEAR 5-check. Escalation trigger to `@improve-prompt` at complexity ≥ 7/10. |\n| `prompt_templates.md` | `TEMPLATES` + `PARALLEL_DETACHED` + `AGENT_DISPATCH` | 13 numbered copy-paste templates per use case/agent (496 lines). Each template names the framework, the invocation shape, and the MEMORY_HANDBACK epilogue structure. |\n\n**Manual Testing Playbook/** — 9 category folders with 31 scenario files (`CO-001` through `CO-031`), rooted in `MANUAL_TESTING_PLAYBOOK.md` as the orchestration guide. Separate from the runtime skill; used for validation only.\n\n### Dependency Flow\n\n```\nSKILL.md (orchestrator)\n  │\n  ├── §2 Smart Router ──────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n  │   │  INTENT_SIGNALS (keyword-weight dict)                       │\n  │   │  RESOURCE_MAP (intent → file list)                          │\n  │   │  LOADING_LEVELS (ALWAYS / CONDITIONAL / ON_DEMAND)          │\n  │   └── delegates helpers to:                                     │\n  │       ../system-spec-kit/references/cli/shared_smart_router.md  │  ← cross-skill shared\n  │\n  ├── ALWAYS-load tier ─────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n  │   ├── references/cli_reference.md        (flags, models, drift) │\n  │   └── assets/prompt_quality_card.md      (framework + CLEAR)    │\n  │\n  ├── CONDITIONAL-load tier (per RESOURCE_MAP intent match) ────────┤\n  │   ├── references/integration_patterns.md (use cases, guard)     │\n  │   ├── references/opencode_tools.md       (capability comparison)│\n  │   └── references/agent_delegation.md     (agent routing matrix) │\n  │\n  ├── ON_DEMAND tier (keyword-triggered) ───────────────────────────┤\n  │   └── assets/prompt_templates.md         (13 copy-paste forms)  │\n  │\n  ├── §3 How It Works ──────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n  │   └── Hardcodes canonical invocation:                           │\n  │       opencode run --model opencode-go/deepseek-v4-pro          │\n  │           --agent general --variant high --format json          │\n  │           --dir <repo-root> \"<prompt>\" 2>&1                     │\n  │\n  ├── §4 Rules ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n  │   │  ALWAYS: guard, pin flags, --format json, </dev/null,       │\n  │   │          spec folder pass-through, prompt quality card       │\n  │   │  NEVER: self-invoke, --share unconfirmed, blind trust,      │\n  │   │         --pure (outside debugging), nested opencode run      │\n  │   │  ESCALATE: not-installed, share URL, version drift,          │\n  │   │            unmapped intent, ambiguous self-invocation        │\n  │   └── Memory Handback →                                         │\n  │       ../system-spec-kit/references/cli/memory_handback.md      │  ← cross-skill shared\n  │\n  ├── graph-metadata.json ──────────────────────────────────────────┤\n  │   └── Consumed by Skill Advisor / Spec Kit Memory (not by       │\n  │       the skill's own runtime logic)                             │\n  │\n  └── manual_testing_playbook/ ─────────────────────────────────────┤\n      └── Rooted in MANUAL_TESTING_PLAYBOOK.md, 31 scenario files    │\n          across 9 categories. NOT loaded at skill runtime.          │\n```\n\n### Notable Conventions\n\n1. **Self-invocation guard (ADR-001).** Three-layer detection (`OPENCODE_*` env vars, `opencode` in process ancestry, `~/.opencode/state/*/lock` files) refuses dispatch when already inside OpenCode. The single exception is use case 2 (parallel detached) with explicit keywords.\n\n2. **Three use cases (ADR-002).** The skill explicitly encodes 3 routes — never a single generic dispatch. The smart router classifies by keyword-weight scoring with an `ambiguity_delta=1.0` threshold for disambiguation.\n\n3. **Shared cross-skill helpers.** Smart router helper functions (`discover_markdown_resources`, `score_intents`, `select_intents`, `route_<provider>_resources`) live in `system-spec-kit/references/cli/shared_smart_router.md` — shared across the entire cli-* family. Memory Handback lives in `system-spec-kit/references/cli/memory_handback.md`.\n\n4. **Resource loading levels.** ALWAYS (2 files), CONDITIONAL (up to 4 intent-mapped files), ON_DEMAND (keyword-triggered). This is a lazy-load pattern — avoids loading 498 lines of prompt templates when the task doesn't need them.\n\n5. **Default invocation shape pinned.** Model (`opencode-go/deepseek-v4-pro`), agent (`general`), variant (`high`), format (`json`), and dir (repo root) are all explicit — nothing is left to the binary's defaults. User overrides honored verbatim.\n\n6. **Prompt quality gate.** Every dispatch prompt must pass through `prompt_quality_card.md`'s CLEAR 5-check before invocation. Complexity ≥ 7/10 triggers an `@improve-prompt` escalation.\n\n7. **Memory Epilogue contract.** Templates include a structured `MEMORY_HANDBACK_START/END` block with typed fields (`specFolder`, `sessionSummary`, `FILES[]`, `nextSteps[]`) that the calling AI extracts and feeds to `generate-context.js`.\n\n8. **Pipeline safety.** `< /dev/null` on backgrounded dispatches in `while read` loops, `2>&1` on all invocations, `--share` requires operator confirmation (CHK-033), `--pure` is debugging-only.\n\n9. **Documentation split.** SKILL.md is the runtime instruction surface (concise, actionable). README.md is the human reference (full FAQ, feature matrix, structure map). The two are complementary — README.md has a full feature catalog and troubleshooting section that SKILL.md only references.\n\n10. **CLI family consistent shape.** All five cli-* skills share the same 8-section SKILL.md structure (when-to-use → smart-routing → how-it-works → rules → references → success-criteria → integration-points → related-resources), the same graph-metadata schema, and the same shared router helpers — enforced by the system-spec-kit validation script.","time":{"start":1777215943375,"end":1777215943375}}}
